  <body><![CDATA[Wow, Alex is right; you totally missed the point of this story...<br /><br />If you know your history then you should know that people at that time would have sent a 'negro' to prison almost without a trial.<br /><br />The purpose of Atticus was to show a contrast of the same people (whites) with different beliefs. He was there to defend a black man instead of being thick headed like some of the other white people.<br /><br />What could the other black people do to defend their kind? Nothing, the white jury would have cared less; Atticus was a white person, and the white jury would have at least thought about a white man's point.<br /><br />This book's purpose (as Helena said) was to show the unfairness of racism during this period of time.]]></body>
  
